    &lt;Title&gt;Lack of communication- appointment cancelled on arrival&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I received numerous confirmations of the appointment, the last being one day prior to my appointment. I followed the preparation and had the day booked off work in order to attend. On arrival I was told that all of the appointments had been cancelled. Considering not being informed of any cancellation, I still attended after the confirmation was received not even 24 hours previously. I have unnecessarily attended which has not only put myself at risk by leaving the house but also my family for no reason. A simple phone call from the clinic to cancel wouldn’t go a miss. I understand that this is a very busy time for healthcare, however cancelling appointments should be high priority to ensure that patients don’t unnecessarily leave their homes only to be told on arrival and in the waiting room that theirs was cancelled. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
